article.description: — Jalen Williams had a career-high 30 points as Santa Clara defeated Hawaii 70-58 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 30 to lift Santa Clara over Hawaii 70-58
article.linkText: Williams scores 30 to lift Santa Clara over Hawaii 70-58
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- — Jalen Williams had a career-high 30 points as Santa Clara defeated Hawaii 70-58 on Tuesday night. Keshawn Justice had 18 points and 10 rebounds for Santa Clara (6-2). Jaden Bediako added nine rebounds. Jerome Desrosiers had 13 points and nine rebounds for the Rainbow Warriors (3-3). Mate Colina added 13 points and 10 rebounds. JoVon McClanahan had 12 points and nine assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
